snippet.textDisplay:
I read a critique of Davis performance in the fight on the grounds that Gamboa was way past his prime. This comes from the same people who criticize Floyd Mayweather's performance when he was schooling current prospects and ranking fighters at the same age as Gamboa and even older. And they are still calling for Floyd to come back and fight young fighters. These people are crazy.

Boxing has become like the larger America where to be black and assertive riles WS. Their insipid hypocrisy is nauseating but expected. From Jack Johnson through early Mohammed Ali to Mayweather the narrative has not changed. It has only become more subtle.
